1
00:01:11,040 --> 00:01:11,720
Hey!

2
00:01:11,720 --> 00:01:13,480
I haven't seen you in so long, Kreetha!

3
00:01:13,480 --> 00:01:16,040
Can I spend a night at your place?

4
00:01:16,040 --> 00:01:17,080
What are you guys doing?

5
00:01:17,080 --> 00:01:18,200
Who's this auntie?

6
00:01:18,200 --> 00:01:19,240
You little fetus ghost!

7
00:01:19,240 --> 00:01:21,240
Ever had your teeth slapped out before?

8
00:01:23,440 --> 00:01:24,280
What is up, Madam?

9
00:01:24,280 --> 00:01:26,480
That damn Glam is getting stronger every day.

10
00:01:26,480 --> 00:01:28,480
I've got no choice but to fight back with something just as powerful.

11
00:01:30,560 --> 00:01:35,560
I...would like to exchange it with Glamorous Airline's information.

12
00:01:38,160 --> 00:01:40,160
You're doomed, Glam!

13
00:01:49,800 --> 00:01:51,520
What are you doing, Madam?

14
00:01:51,520 --> 00:01:52,440
I'm looking at an automaton.

15
00:01:52,440 --> 00:01:56,440
Whoa! Is that AI-related? You're so trendy.

16
00:01:56,800 --> 00:01:59,160
But what do you need that for?

17
00:01:59,160 --> 00:02:01,320
To replace you.

18
00:02:01,320 --> 00:02:03,080
What did I do wrong, Madam?

19
00:02:03,080 --> 00:02:06,960
The automaton won't stick his nose into my business.

20
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:08,960
So what kind of an automaton will you buy?

21
00:02:11,040 --> 00:02:13,280
I'll buy a Thai spirit automaton.

22
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:16,480
Do you need to go that far, Madam?

23
00:02:16,480 --> 00:02:20,480
I've been too soft on them...

24
00:02:20,920 --> 00:02:22,600
If the gentle way didn't work...

25
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:25,040
why don't you bring out the broom next?

26
00:02:25,040 --> 00:02:28,120
That's a good idea. My house has been a mess these days...

27
00:02:28,120 --> 00:02:30,280
Hey, Siri! What was that?

28
00:02:30,280 --> 00:02:33,680
That damn Glam is getting stronger every day.

29
00:02:33,680 --> 00:02:36,600
I've got no choice but to fight back with something just as powerful.

30
00:02:36,600 --> 00:02:39,240
Something just as powerful...like what, exactly?

31
00:02:39,240 --> 00:02:41,480
Racing cars, jet-skis...

32
00:02:41,480 --> 00:02:44,360
Wait, what? Siri!

33
00:02:44,360 --> 00:02:46,520
Stop it and listen to me!

34
00:02:46,520 --> 00:02:50,000
Find me a Thai spirit automaton.

35
00:02:50,720 --> 00:02:54,320
What exactly does an automaton do?

36
00:02:54,320 --> 00:02:58,360
With cursed materials from spirits and corpses dug up from graveyards,

37
00:02:58,360 --> 00:03:01,880
the power of the automaton becomes terrifyingly strong.

38
00:03:01,880 --> 00:03:04,840
If stabbed with needles or slashed with sharp objects,

39
00:03:04,840 --> 00:03:07,280
burned in fire or buried deep in the cemetery,

40
00:03:07,280 --> 00:03:10,520
the one tied to those dark materials will suffer in agony.

41
00:03:10,520 --> 00:03:12,840
They’ll face destruction, business ruined,

42
00:03:12,840 --> 00:03:13,640
fall off tables,

43
00:03:13,640 --> 00:03:14,400
fall of beds,

44
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:15,240
fall of cabinets,

45
00:03:15,240 --> 00:03:17,440
fail exams, get bitten by toads,

46
00:03:17,440 --> 00:03:19,520
get strangled by snakes, cut by fan blades...

47
00:03:19,520 --> 00:03:21,800
Madam! You're turning it into a song!

48
00:03:21,800 --> 00:03:23,400
You really can't concentrate today.

49
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:27,400
You gotta find me an automaton, no matter what!

50
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:31,000
You're doomed, Glam!

51
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:40,880
Hey!

52
00:03:40,880 --> 00:03:41,520
Yes?

53
00:03:41,520 --> 00:03:43,360
Tid-Gift, what's wrong? Why are you walking like that?

54
00:03:43,360 --> 00:03:45,880
These shoes are giving me blisters.

55
00:03:45,880 --> 00:03:47,960
I tried loosening them first...

56
00:03:47,960 --> 00:03:48,960
but they're still hurting me.

57
00:03:49,920 --> 00:03:50,920
Let me see...

58
00:04:13,520 --> 00:04:14,520
Kreetha...

59
00:04:18,920 --> 00:04:19,920
Yes, Tid-Gift.

60
00:04:27,200 --> 00:04:29,320
That's the wrong side.

61
00:04:29,320 --> 00:04:30,360
Well, you didn't tell me.

62
00:04:30,360 --> 00:04:33,360
My wound’s on the right side, how could you put it on the left?

63
00:04:35,440 --> 00:04:37,920
This is taking too long.

64
00:04:37,920 --> 00:04:39,920
The bandage’s probably dried out by now.

65
00:04:43,160 --> 00:04:45,160
Anyway, thanks a lot...you silly puppy.

66
00:04:47,240 --> 00:04:51,240
Well then, would you be interested in adopting a puppy like me?

67
00:04:55,560 --> 00:04:57,560
What are you even saying?

68
00:05:04,360 --> 00:05:07,600
Gift, the thing is...

69
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:09,600
Are you hitting on me, Kreetha?

70
00:05:12,320 --> 00:05:16,320
I'm trying to put these away, not put these in.

71
00:05:18,240 --> 00:05:19,240
Oh...

72
00:05:35,560 --> 00:05:36,280
Chaba.

73
00:05:36,280 --> 00:05:37,400
Huh?

74
00:05:37,400 --> 00:05:38,560
You’re paying today.

75
00:05:38,560 --> 00:05:39,800
Why?

76
00:05:39,800 --> 00:05:43,720
My banking app isn’t working.

77
00:05:43,720 --> 00:05:44,760
Oh please, quit pretending.

78
00:05:44,760 --> 00:05:46,720
You literally opened the camera app instead.

79
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:48,920
You're broke, okay? You can say it.

80
00:05:48,920 --> 00:05:49,920
No shame here.

81
00:05:52,080 --> 00:05:54,160
I’m dead broke this month.

82
00:05:54,160 --> 00:05:55,920
I’ve got zero spending money, seriously.

83
00:05:55,920 --> 00:05:57,080
Mmm.

84
00:05:57,080 --> 00:06:01,080
By the way, can you lend me like 5,000?

85
00:06:01,240 --> 00:06:03,840
And where exactly am I supposed to pull that from?

86
00:06:03,840 --> 00:06:07,840
Wasn’t it you who dragged me shopping till we went broke?

87
00:06:09,760 --> 00:06:11,240
Ugh, I’m so over this.

88
00:06:13,440 --> 00:06:16,160
Thinking of borrowing from Mom again...but I did that last month already.

89
00:06:16,160 --> 00:06:17,600
I’ve maxed out everything.

90
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:20,840
Credit card’s blacklisted too.

91
00:06:20,840 --> 00:06:22,520
How the hell am I gonna survive the rest of the month?

92
00:06:22,520 --> 00:06:23,520
Exactly.

93
00:06:27,400 --> 00:06:31,400
Miji, look at those two, remember them?

94
00:06:31,840 --> 00:06:34,280
Madam, I’m not that old, I don’t have Alzheimer’s.

95
00:06:34,280 --> 00:06:38,280
Those two, they're flight attendants at Glamorous, remember?

96
00:06:39,360 --> 00:06:41,880
Of all the days I’ve known you, today you’re the smartest.

97
00:06:43,360 --> 00:06:45,360
Thank you, Madam. Rare moment when you actually compliment me.

98
00:06:49,960 --> 00:06:50,960
Hello there.

99
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:57,960
Do you girls remember me?

100
00:06:57,960 --> 00:06:58,640
Sky, oh my god...

101
00:06:58,920 --> 00:07:00,920
Isn’t that the woman?

102
00:07:03,520 --> 00:07:04,600
Don’t be scared.

103
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:07,120
I didn’t bring anything with me today.

104
00:07:07,120 --> 00:07:08,120
Except this.

105
00:07:10,840 --> 00:07:11,840
Put that away!

106
00:07:14,080 --> 00:07:15,080
Don’t be alarmed.

107
00:07:16,040 --> 00:07:18,960
I’m not here to do anything today.

108
00:07:18,960 --> 00:07:22,960
Just wanted to get to know you girls, that’s all.

109
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:25,640
Yeah, yeah. Hi there.

110
00:07:25,640 --> 00:07:28,160
Hello.

111
00:07:28,160 --> 00:07:30,160
May I join you?

112
00:07:32,280 --> 00:07:34,080
Please, go ahead. Have a seat.

113
00:07:34,080 --> 00:07:36,080
How sweet of you, thank you.

114
00:07:42,120 --> 00:07:44,120
Oops, it's just the chair, sorry.

115
00:07:44,120 --> 00:07:45,520
That startled me. I’m kinda jumpy, you know.

116
00:07:45,520 --> 00:07:46,480
Sensitive soul, fragile heart.

117
00:07:46,480 --> 00:07:47,480
Right...

118
00:08:02,040 --> 00:08:03,040
Miji.

119
00:08:03,520 --> 00:08:06,520
We really startled you...

120
00:08:06,520 --> 00:08:08,520
You’re not carrying a gun, are you?

121
00:08:08,520 --> 00:08:10,520
No. Didn’t bring one.

122
00:08:47,720 --> 00:08:50,160
Oh, Sai Eiam!

123
00:08:50,160 --> 00:08:53,720
Hey! Wow!

124
00:08:53,720 --> 00:08:54,720
What is it?

125
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:58,280
What's the matter with you?

126
00:08:58,280 --> 00:08:59,240
You're so adorable!

127
00:08:59,240 --> 00:09:01,240
Haven't seen you in forever, Kreetha!

128
00:09:02,640 --> 00:09:05,000
Don't tell me...

129
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:06,960
your dad sent you to collect the debt...

130
00:09:06,960 --> 00:09:09,000
Let me tell you...

131
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:11,000
I don't have it right now.

132
00:09:19,800 --> 00:09:23,200
Well, if you don't have the money...

133
00:09:23,200 --> 00:09:27,200
you can pay me with other things instead.

134
00:09:27,960 --> 00:09:28,960
Other things?

135
00:09:32,960 --> 00:09:35,720
But...I've never done it before...

136
00:09:35,720 --> 00:09:36,720
C'mon, let's go!

137
00:09:38,560 --> 00:09:39,480
Come on!

138
00:09:39,480 --> 00:09:40,040
No!

139
00:09:40,040 --> 00:09:40,480
C'mon!

140
00:09:40,480 --> 00:09:41,080
No, I'm not going.

141
00:09:41,080 --> 00:09:42,080
Let's go!

142
00:09:46,200 --> 00:09:48,280
Girls, don't be scared.

143
00:09:48,280 --> 00:09:51,360
That day, I really didn't mean to, you know.

144
00:09:51,360 --> 00:09:52,520
It was an accident.

145
00:09:52,520 --> 00:09:55,200
I was a little drunk.

146
00:09:55,200 --> 00:09:56,200
Oh.

147
00:09:57,720 --> 00:10:01,240
Hmm, what should I do? You girls seem to be scared.

148
00:10:01,240 --> 00:10:06,680
How about I treat you to a meal today to cheer you up?

149
00:10:08,360 --> 00:10:10,240
Ooh, that sounds great!

150
00:10:10,240 --> 00:10:14,240
Then let me officially introduce myself.

151
00:10:14,360 --> 00:10:17,680
I’m Pam. And this is...

152
00:10:17,680 --> 00:10:19,120
Miji.

153
00:10:19,120 --> 00:10:22,760
And this is Ma...oops! I mean, Pam. I'm Pam's junior.

154
00:10:22,760 --> 00:10:23,920
Nice to meet you.

155
00:10:23,920 --> 00:10:25,320
Hello!

156
00:10:25,320 --> 00:10:28,560
Sky, who even names their kid Miji?

157
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:33,120
From your accent...

158
00:10:33,120 --> 00:10:35,720
are you half-Japanese?

159
00:10:35,720 --> 00:10:39,720
Yes, but I can’t speak that much Japanese.

160
00:10:41,920 --> 00:10:45,920
Kimono, kattewa, Ajinomoto...

161
00:10:47,800 --> 00:10:51,800
Oishi, Shinkansen, Ikkyu-san, ikuitai, Daifuku...

162
00:10:55,600 --> 00:10:57,960
Ohayo gozaimasu.

163
00:10:57,960 --> 00:11:01,160
onojayama. Sadhu no bhante, bhikku-sangho.

164
00:11:01,160 --> 00:11:03,280
Whoa whoa, Miji, hold on.

165
00:11:03,280 --> 00:11:07,280
I think that was a bit too long for an introduction.

166
00:11:07,920 --> 00:11:11,040
Look at you! You talked like someone who's never had friends.

167
00:11:11,040 --> 00:11:12,720
Ouch! That hurts!

168
00:11:12,720 --> 00:11:16,120
Why did you pinch me?

169
00:11:16,120 --> 00:11:20,120
That really hurt, you know.

170
00:11:20,960 --> 00:11:25,920
By the way, I don’t know your names yet.

171
00:11:25,920 --> 00:11:27,440
You’re both so beautiful!

172
00:11:27,440 --> 00:11:30,880
Hi, I’m Sky.

173
00:11:30,880 --> 00:11:32,600
Hello, I’m Chaba.

174
00:11:32,600 --> 00:11:36,440
Oh my, such cute names! So adorable.

175
00:11:36,440 --> 00:11:42,520
So what do pretty girls like you two do for work?

176
00:11:42,520 --> 00:11:45,960
Well, I’m a flight attendant.

177
00:11:45,960 --> 00:11:48,920
Ooh, a flight attendant!

178
00:11:48,920 --> 00:11:52,480
Let me guess, with that kind of beauty…

179
00:11:52,480 --> 00:11:57,480
you must be flying with Glamorous Airline, right?

180
00:11:58,440 --> 00:12:02,280
Whoa, are you a secret agent or something?

181
00:12:02,280 --> 00:12:04,760
Come on, it’s obvious!

182
00:12:04,760 --> 00:12:06,400
Because Glamorous Airline...

183
00:12:06,400 --> 00:12:09,720
...is super high-standard, right?

184
00:12:09,720 --> 00:12:11,960
They’re very selective with their crew.

185
00:12:11,960 --> 00:12:15,120
The owner must be a total perfectionist, right?

186
00:12:15,120 --> 00:12:16,880
Yeah, totally.

187
00:12:16,880 --> 00:12:19,080
He’s a real perfectionist.

188
00:12:19,080 --> 00:12:20,640
Oh, really?

189
00:12:20,640 --> 00:12:21,440
Yes.

190
00:12:21,440 --> 00:12:23,840
Has he ever been here?

191
00:12:23,840 --> 00:12:27,840
Hmm…why are you so interested in Glamourous, Pam?

192
00:12:29,240 --> 00:12:35,800
Oh, it’s because my niece wants to become a flight attendant.

193
00:12:35,800 --> 00:12:39,240
So of course, we’re eyeing the best airline possible.

194
00:12:39,240 --> 00:12:40,000
That’s great!

195
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:42,840
Because Glamorous Airline is the most fabulous airline of our era.

196
00:12:42,840 --> 00:12:44,840
Everyone wants to work with them.

197
00:12:45,840 --> 00:12:46,840
Here comes the lies bomb!

198
00:12:49,120 --> 00:12:51,360
Aww, it's a pom! Puppy, you’re so cute!

199
00:12:51,360 --> 00:12:53,360
Oh look! Quick! He’s running over there!

200
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:56,200
Miji, would you stop?

201
00:12:58,640 --> 00:13:01,280
But the more I look...

202
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:05,320
Sky, you’ve got such a lovely face.

203
00:13:05,320 --> 00:13:08,320
And your skin, it's flawless! So smooth...

204
00:13:08,320 --> 00:13:10,320
like you’ve never been exposed to the sun or wind.

205
00:13:12,040 --> 00:13:13,040
Oh, I don’t think so.

206
00:13:14,600 --> 00:13:16,160
Adorable. You're just so adorable!

207
00:13:16,160 --> 00:13:19,480
And Chaba, your body is amazing!

208
00:13:19,480 --> 00:13:22,440
You look like someone who drinks four liters of clean water a day.

209
00:13:22,440 --> 00:13:24,440
And probably works out every morning too, right?

210
00:13:26,400 --> 00:13:29,360
Pam, you seriously see through everything!

211
00:13:29,360 --> 00:13:30,440
So true.

212
00:13:30,440 --> 00:13:33,000
Ooh, let me guess one more thing...

213
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:37,000
Chaba, you’re a vegetarian, aren’t you?

214
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:37,880
How did you know?

215
00:13:37,880 --> 00:13:40,600
Exactly. She hasn't eaten meat in nine years.

216
00:13:40,600 --> 00:13:41,600
That’s right.

217
00:13:41,920 --> 00:13:43,000
Nobody ever knows that.

218
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:45,560
I could tell at a glance!

219
00:13:45,560 --> 00:13:47,640
You’ve got sharp eyes, Pam.

220
00:13:47,640 --> 00:13:51,600
You know what? I’m honestly so happy today.

221
00:13:51,600 --> 00:13:54,240
So let’s not eat here.

222
00:13:54,240 --> 00:13:57,920
Let’s go find something really tasty instead!

223
00:13:57,920 --> 00:14:00,480
My treat, I'm covering the bill

224
00:14:00,480 --> 00:14:02,760
Yaaas, love it! That's fab!

225
00:14:02,760 --> 00:14:03,680
Alright, let’s go. What are you waiting for?

226
00:14:03,680 --> 00:14:04,320
Shall we?

227
00:14:04,320 --> 00:14:06,200
Oh wow, so quick!

228
00:14:06,800 --> 00:14:07,400
Grab your bag, darling.

229
00:14:07,400 --> 00:14:08,320
Let’s go, let’s go!

230
00:14:08,320 --> 00:14:09,000
After you, please!

231
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:09,640
Let’s go, Pam!

232
00:14:09,640 --> 00:14:12,440
Which restaurant should we go to?
This way might be better. Over there’s just full of...

233
00:14:15,680 --> 00:14:16,280
Let’s go!

234
00:14:16,280 --> 00:14:16,960
What? Go where?

235
00:14:16,960 --> 00:14:17,840
Hurry up. Just come on!

236
00:14:17,840 --> 00:14:20,760
I’m not going. What’s going on?

237
00:14:20,760 --> 00:14:22,440
What’s up with you, Sai Eiam?

238
00:14:22,440 --> 00:14:26,160
Gosh, why overthink it? I just want us to go out.

239
00:14:26,160 --> 00:14:27,360
Not like I’m asking for anything more.

240
00:14:27,360 --> 00:14:29,160
Don't be so naughty.

241
00:14:29,840 --> 00:14:31,400
Come on, let’s go.

242
00:14:31,400 --> 00:14:32,680
Nope. Not going.

243
00:14:32,680 --> 00:14:33,520
Go!

244
00:14:33,520 --> 00:14:34,760
Nope. I'm not going anywhere.

245
00:14:34,760 --> 00:14:35,560
Hurry!

246
00:14:35,560 --> 00:14:36,200
For real!

247
00:14:36,200 --> 00:14:37,400
Sai Eiam, what’s your deal?

248
00:14:37,400 --> 00:14:39,400
Hey! What’s going on here?

249
00:14:42,760 --> 00:14:45,480
Kreetha, who is this old hag?

250
00:14:45,480 --> 00:14:47,120
Excuse me, brat!

251
00:14:47,120 --> 00:14:48,760
A mouth like that needs to be...

252
00:14:48,760 --> 00:14:49,720
Who is she?

253
00:14:49,720 --> 00:14:50,720
Uhh…

254
00:14:53,080 --> 00:14:54,160
What’s wrong?

255
00:14:54,160 --> 00:14:57,120
Sai Eiam, what is it with you?

256
00:14:57,120 --> 00:14:58,280
I...

257
00:14:58,280 --> 00:15:01,520
I’m scared of her wrinkles.

258
00:15:01,520 --> 00:15:02,520
I’m panicking. I might faint.

259
00:15:04,640 --> 00:15:06,520
Hey! Who’s this tofu-faced kid?

260
00:15:06,520 --> 00:15:08,240
Wait, ever get slapped?

261
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:09,680
Oh, wait, she’s my friend.

262
00:15:09,680 --> 00:15:10,680
She’s with me.

263
00:15:12,080 --> 00:15:13,560
A friend, huh, Kreetha?

264
00:15:13,560 --> 00:15:15,560
I'm your girlfriend. Tell her!

265
00:15:22,960 --> 00:15:26,400
Let’s go, Kreetha. The air here is getting toxic.

266
00:15:26,400 --> 00:15:28,400
Smells like...old people.

267
00:15:32,120 --> 00:15:35,320
You little devil, you clearly don’t know what I'm capable of!

268
00:15:35,320 --> 00:15:36,320
You’re gonna regret this.

269
00:15:38,040 --> 00:15:40,040
Is that your mouth or a garbage chute?

270
00:15:48,440 --> 00:15:49,720
Miji.

271
00:15:49,720 --> 00:15:52,440
Everyone’s been staring at me today.

272
00:15:52,440 --> 00:15:54,440
I must look absolutely stunning, right?

273
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:59,000
Madam, dressed like that? They’d be crazy not to look.

274
00:16:04,040 --> 00:16:04,520
Chaba.

275
00:16:04,520 --> 00:16:06,280
Yeah?

276
00:16:06,280 --> 00:16:07,400
What?

277
00:16:07,400 --> 00:16:08,840
Look over there.

278
00:16:08,840 --> 00:16:09,600
Where?

279
00:16:09,600 --> 00:16:10,600
There!

280
00:16:12,080 --> 00:16:14,720
Oh! Is that Pam?

281
00:16:14,720 --> 00:16:15,720
Yeah.

282
00:16:17,160 --> 00:16:18,880
So what’s the plan today?

283
00:16:18,880 --> 00:16:20,360
Are we getting another free meal?

284
00:16:20,360 --> 00:16:21,360
Hell yeah.

285
00:16:22,400 --> 00:16:24,160
Hi, Pam!

286
00:16:24,160 --> 00:16:25,360
Hello!

287
00:16:25,360 --> 00:16:27,240
Didn’t think we’d run into you again!

288
00:16:27,240 --> 00:16:31,160
Oh! Sky and Chaba!

289
00:16:31,160 --> 00:16:34,960
What a surprise! We meet again!

290
00:16:34,960 --> 00:16:37,360
Where are you two headed all dressed up like that?

291
00:16:37,360 --> 00:16:40,840
Wearing fur and sparkling like crystal candy!

292
00:16:40,840 --> 00:16:44,320
We’re flying to Hong Kong.

293
00:16:44,320 --> 00:16:46,280
Hong Kong?

294
00:16:46,280 --> 00:16:49,720
Oh my! What a coincidence!

295
00:16:49,720 --> 00:16:52,200
I’m flying to Hong Kong too, same flight!

296
00:16:52,200 --> 00:16:54,440
Oh wow! Oh my god!

297
00:16:54,440 --> 00:16:55,240
Total coincidence!

298
00:16:55,240 --> 00:16:59,040
Wow, this isn’t just random.

299
00:16:59,040 --> 00:17:02,280
Call it fate or destiny, who knows?

300
00:17:02,280 --> 00:17:05,680
But for me...

301
00:17:05,680 --> 00:17:08,440
I’d say it’s soulmate-level destiny!

302
00:17:08,440 --> 00:17:09,320
Right...

303
00:17:09,320 --> 00:17:11,080
Another lies bomb.

304
00:17:11,080 --> 00:17:14,880
My screen is bombing, no idea what’s wrong.

305
00:17:14,880 --> 00:17:16,320
Ugh, Madam!

306
00:17:16,320 --> 00:17:20,320
You keep slapping and pinching me, I’m bruised all over!

307
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:25,120
So I’m going shopping...

308
00:17:25,120 --> 00:17:27,680
Pray to the Goddess of Mercy...

309
00:17:27,680 --> 00:17:29,680
Look for that famous Pixiu...

310
00:17:29,680 --> 00:17:31,680
Find the red string of fate...

311
00:17:31,680 --> 00:17:33,320
the lucky windmill...

312
00:17:33,320 --> 00:17:35,520
And grab a money-attracting gourd!

313
00:17:35,520 --> 00:17:39,520
It’d be so much fun if you girls came along!

314
00:17:41,480 --> 00:17:43,680
I was thinking the same!

315
00:17:43,680 --> 00:17:46,640
Madam, this was your plan, wasn’t it?

316
00:17:46,640 --> 00:17:48,640
How did you know we’d run into them?

317
00:17:52,080 --> 00:17:54,480
Hey, All-New!

318
00:17:54,480 --> 00:17:55,880
Am I seeing things?

319
00:17:55,880 --> 00:17:57,680
You're working out?

320
00:17:57,680 --> 00:17:58,880
You’re not seeing things.

321
00:17:58,880 --> 00:17:59,920
I’m at the gym.

322
00:17:59,920 --> 00:18:02,560
I told you to find something on Glam, and you’re hitting the gym?

323
00:18:02,560 --> 00:18:04,440
Well, you said to follow Mr. Hot.

324
00:18:04,440 --> 00:18:07,560
Turns out Mr. Glam owns a gym in the U.S.

325
00:18:07,560 --> 00:18:09,320
So I'm here undercover.

326
00:18:09,320 --> 00:18:12,160
Hmm. Good job, All-New.

327
00:18:12,160 --> 00:18:15,640
Wait a minute. Since when do you know how to work out?

328
00:18:15,640 --> 00:18:17,240
There’s nothing too hard for me.

329
00:18:17,240 --> 00:18:19,640
Hey, All-New, I’ve got an urgent matter I need your help with.

330
00:18:19,640 --> 00:18:21,120
What is it, Madam? Just say it.

331
00:18:21,120 --> 00:18:24,360
I want you to take care of the Glamorous flight for me.

332
00:18:24,880 --> 00:18:26,280
Do whatever you have to do...

333
00:18:26,280 --> 00:18:31,160
just make sure I’m on the same flight
as the flight attendants named Sky and Chaba. Can you do that?

334
00:18:31,160 --> 00:18:33,440
Whoa, is that all?

335
00:18:33,440 --> 00:18:34,440
Easy. I got this.

336
00:18:35,280 --> 00:18:36,280
Great. You’re amazing.

337
00:18:37,840 --> 00:18:38,840
Piece of cake.

338
00:18:56,800 --> 00:19:00,320
Sky and Chaba, why don't you have a seat and chat first?

339
00:19:00,720 --> 00:19:01,720
Sure.

340
00:19:03,160 --> 00:19:05,760
Wow, your outfit is so pretty!

341
00:19:05,760 --> 00:19:07,520
It’s glamourous.

342
00:19:07,520 --> 00:19:11,440
Oh! I’ve heard people talk about Glamorous Airline before,

343
00:19:11,440 --> 00:19:14,080
but I’ve never seen the owner.

344
00:19:14,080 --> 00:19:15,680
Is the owner really that mysterious?

345
00:19:15,680 --> 00:19:16,400
Oh!

346
00:19:16,400 --> 00:19:17,720
You mean Mr. Glam?

347
00:19:17,720 --> 00:19:19,440
Others might say he’s mysterious,

348
00:19:19,440 --> 00:19:22,040
but for us...

349
00:19:22,040 --> 00:19:24,080
we’re super close.

350
00:19:24,080 --> 00:19:26,760
So what does this Mr. Glam look like?

351
00:19:26,760 --> 00:19:30,120
Oh my, if you’re talking about our Boss Glam...

352
00:19:30,120 --> 00:19:33,840
he’s one of a kind, you could find a man like him once in a hundred years.

353
00:19:33,840 --> 00:19:36,840
Tall, lean, long legs. Narrow eyes behind glasses.

354
00:19:36,840 --> 00:19:39,280
Mazda lips, cockle eyes.

355
00:19:39,280 --> 00:19:40,280
I don’t think that’s real.

356
00:19:42,440 --> 00:19:43,440
Just kidding.

357
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:45,000
He’s handsome.

358
00:19:45,760 --> 00:19:48,360
Asian-looking, kind of like that.

359
00:19:48,360 --> 00:19:49,360
Got it now.

360
00:19:51,360 --> 00:19:53,680
Hey Chaba, don’t you think...

361
00:19:53,680 --> 00:19:56,680
once you think of Hong Kong, it’s all about...

362
00:19:57,120 --> 00:19:59,680
designer brands and all that, right?

363
00:19:59,680 --> 00:20:01,520
Exactly.

364
00:20:01,520 --> 00:20:05,040
Will I ever be lucky enough...

365
00:20:05,040 --> 00:20:07,120
to wear branded stuff?

366
00:20:07,120 --> 00:20:09,720
All I’ve got now is knockoffs.

367
00:20:09,720 --> 00:20:11,760
Aw, poor thing.

368
00:20:11,760 --> 00:20:14,840
So girls, which brand do you want?

369
00:20:14,840 --> 00:20:16,760
Oh...

370
00:20:16,760 --> 00:20:18,520
No, it’s okay.

371
00:20:18,520 --> 00:20:22,520
Um... Alexander Wang or something like that?

372
00:20:22,920 --> 00:20:26,920
Ah, Alexander Wang.

373
00:20:28,120 --> 00:20:30,120
Don’t tell me, Pam...

374
00:20:30,120 --> 00:20:32,120
Don’t worry, dear.

375
00:20:35,080 --> 00:20:37,520
I wear size 36 shoes.

376
00:20:37,520 --> 00:20:39,960
And this one? Size 49, right?

377
00:20:39,960 --> 00:20:42,120
Wow, such big feet.

378
00:20:42,120 --> 00:20:43,560
They’re still growing.

379
00:20:43,560 --> 00:20:47,560
No problem. I'm actually their super VIP customer.

380
00:20:48,720 --> 00:20:50,120
Oh, really?

381
00:20:50,120 --> 00:20:50,840
We’re close.

382
00:20:50,840 --> 00:20:52,840
No wonder, you're glowing.

383
00:20:56,640 --> 00:20:58,400
But it’s time for us to fly, Sky.

384
00:20:58,400 --> 00:20:59,360
Oh, you’re right!

385
00:20:59,360 --> 00:21:02,040
Well then, see you onboard, Pam, Miji.

386
00:21:02,040 --> 00:21:02,840
Ah, okay.

387
00:21:02,840 --> 00:21:04,720
See you. Goodbye, Ma’am.

388
00:21:04,720 --> 00:21:07,120
Goodbye. See you on the flight.

389
00:21:07,120 --> 00:21:08,120
You got it!

390
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:10,000
See you onboard!

391
00:21:10,280 --> 00:21:11,280
Okay!

392
00:21:15,440 --> 00:21:17,440
And yet, you never hug me...

393
00:21:41,680 --> 00:21:42,640
Hello, yes?

394
00:21:42,640 --> 00:21:43,840
Hello, Kreetha.

395
00:21:43,840 --> 00:21:44,760
Where are you?

396
00:21:44,760 --> 00:21:45,800
I’m at a bar.

397
00:21:45,800 --> 00:21:47,000
Oh, really?

398
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:48,240
Yeah.

399
00:21:48,240 --> 00:21:50,640
I brought Sai Eiam out to hang.

400
00:21:51,120 --> 00:21:52,120
Oh!

401
00:22:02,320 --> 00:22:06,360
Wow, the restroom here is so comfy, right?

402
00:22:06,360 --> 00:22:07,360
Mm-hmm.

403
00:22:11,360 --> 00:22:13,320
Oh, right...

404
00:22:13,320 --> 00:22:16,480
Kreetha, I still don’t know where I’ll sleep tonight.

405
00:22:16,480 --> 00:22:20,240
Can I spend a night at your place?

406
00:22:20,240 --> 00:22:22,720
Sai Eiam? Is that a good idea?

407
00:22:22,720 --> 00:22:24,720
I don’t mind.

408
00:22:40,360 --> 00:22:41,600
Hello, Dad?

409
00:22:41,600 --> 00:22:43,960
Sai Eiam, come home right now!

410
00:22:43,960 --> 00:22:47,000
Ugh, Dad! I’ve only been here for one day.

411
00:22:47,000 --> 00:22:48,480
I haven’t even collected any debts yet!

412
00:22:48,480 --> 00:22:51,680
Can I stay for like, two or three more days, please?

413
00:22:51,680 --> 00:22:52,960
Please, Dad? Pretty please?

414
00:22:52,960 --> 00:22:53,760
No.

415
00:22:53,760 --> 00:22:57,080
Aw, thank you, Dad! Goodnight. Muah muah!

416
00:22:57,080 --> 00:22:58,080
Sai Eiam!

417
00:23:03,000 --> 00:23:05,280
Ugh, why are you pouting?

418
00:23:05,280 --> 00:23:07,560
Dance, come on!

419
00:23:07,560 --> 00:23:09,720
Move it, dance!

420
00:23:09,720 --> 00:23:13,200
Shake your shoulders, left and right!

421
00:23:13,200 --> 00:23:14,800
Or you don’t like it?

422
00:23:14,800 --> 00:23:16,880
Oh, you like 4EVE songs, huh?

423
00:23:16,880 --> 00:23:18,040
They just had a comeback.

424
00:23:18,040 --> 00:23:20,160
Whoa, cool taste, you should’ve said!

425
00:23:20,160 --> 00:23:21,160
Dance more!

426
00:23:23,400 --> 00:23:24,400
Hey!

427
00:23:24,880 --> 00:23:26,880
Mind if I sit here?

428
00:23:28,960 --> 00:23:30,960
Oops, wrong place?

429
00:23:32,200 --> 00:23:35,400
This is a club, not a senior center.

430
00:23:35,400 --> 00:23:36,880
You little fetus ghost!

431
00:23:36,880 --> 00:23:39,360
Ever had your teeth slapped out?

432
00:23:39,360 --> 00:23:42,160
Hey, Tid-Gift, what year is it now?

433
00:23:42,160 --> 00:23:44,160
Stop using violence already.

434
00:23:45,400 --> 00:23:47,640
If you want to compete,

435
00:23:47,640 --> 00:23:49,640
why don’t we try something else?

436
00:23:52,880 --> 00:23:53,880
Fine.

437
00:23:54,240 --> 00:23:55,240
Bring it on.

438
00:24:04,360 --> 00:24:05,360
Vodka contest!

439
00:24:06,360 --> 00:24:08,360
If you're ready, go!

440
00:24:09,440 --> 00:24:10,440
Tid-Gift!

441
00:24:13,520 --> 00:24:14,520
Sai Eiam!

442
00:24:19,520 --> 00:24:20,520
Tid-Gift!

443
00:24:31,080 --> 00:24:32,400
Hey, stop, stop, stop!

444
00:24:32,400 --> 00:24:34,560
Stop! Put it down!

445
00:24:34,560 --> 00:24:35,920
You know what?

446
00:24:35,920 --> 00:24:38,600
This is just a waste of vodka.

447
00:24:38,600 --> 00:24:40,680
You two are like...

448
00:24:40,680 --> 00:24:42,440
alcohol-slaying machines!

449
00:24:42,440 --> 00:24:43,440
Let’s do something else.

450
00:24:46,000 --> 00:24:47,000
Okay!

451
00:24:53,520 --> 00:24:55,520
Ready? Go!

452
00:25:23,160 --> 00:25:25,160
And the winner is Tid-Gift!

453
00:25:27,200 --> 00:25:28,240
Cheater!

454
00:25:28,240 --> 00:25:28,720
What?

455
00:25:28,720 --> 00:25:29,480
You cheated!

456
00:25:29,480 --> 00:25:30,280
How?

457
00:25:30,280 --> 00:25:30,960
Cheater!

458
00:25:30,960 --> 00:25:31,600
I’ll cheat if I want!

459
00:25:31,600 --> 00:25:32,240
You cheated!

460
00:25:32,240 --> 00:25:32,960
That’s my business.

461
00:25:32,960 --> 00:25:34,320
C-H-E-A-T.

462
00:25:34,320 --> 00:25:35,080
You just lost.

463
00:25:35,080 --> 00:25:35,840
You cheated!

464
00:25:35,840 --> 00:25:36,440
You lost!

465
00:25:36,440 --> 00:25:37,120
You cheated!

466
00:25:40,320 --> 00:25:43,160
Whatever! Next round’s my pick.

467
00:25:43,160 --> 00:25:44,400
Bring it on!

468
00:25:44,400 --> 00:25:45,400
Fine!

469
00:25:56,400 --> 00:25:57,960
Hey, Sky...

470
00:25:57,960 --> 00:26:00,840
do you think Pam will really buy us branded stuff?

471
00:26:01,960 --> 00:26:03,560
I think she will.

472
00:26:04,200 --> 00:26:08,200
Rich folks like that barely have friends.

473
00:26:09,280 --> 00:26:11,760
They love gifting stuff to people.

474
00:26:14,080 --> 00:26:15,320
That’s actually not bad.

475
00:26:15,320 --> 00:26:17,320
So what should we ask Pam to buy us next time?

476
00:26:19,240 --> 00:26:21,120
Go big, shall we?

477
00:26:22,200 --> 00:26:23,400
Hello?

478
00:26:24,480 --> 00:26:27,200
Pam, what brings you here?

479
00:26:27,200 --> 00:26:30,720
Well, I was sitting out there for so long I got bored.

480
00:26:30,720 --> 00:26:33,440
Then I heard you two chatting,

481
00:26:33,440 --> 00:26:35,600
so I thought I’d come join you.

482
00:26:35,600 --> 00:26:37,960
Maybe we can find something fun to do together.

483
00:26:37,960 --> 00:26:38,960
Oh.

484
00:26:39,160 --> 00:26:42,720
Like what?

485
00:26:42,720 --> 00:26:45,400
Do you girls like fortune-telling?

486
00:26:45,400 --> 00:26:46,600
Ooh, love it!

487
00:26:46,600 --> 00:26:48,200
I'm really good at reading fortunes.

488
00:26:48,200 --> 00:26:49,160
Oh, really?

489
00:26:49,160 --> 00:26:51,480
Want me to read your career path? I can do that.

490
00:26:51,480 --> 00:26:53,200
Ooh, yes, please! That’d be great!

491
00:26:53,200 --> 00:26:54,720
But...

492
00:26:54,720 --> 00:26:58,320
I forgot to bring my cards.

493
00:26:58,320 --> 00:27:01,280
That's totally fine because I have the cards here.

494
00:27:01,280 --> 00:27:02,280
Oh! Perfect.

495
00:27:08,720 --> 00:27:09,720
Go ahead.

496
00:27:10,200 --> 00:27:12,880
I swear this feels familiar.

497
00:27:12,880 --> 00:27:13,520
Sit, quick.

498
00:27:13,520 --> 00:27:14,520
Ah, okay.

499
00:27:17,800 --> 00:27:20,200
Cut the deck with your non-dominant hand.

500
00:27:20,200 --> 00:27:21,440
Can I use my dominant hand instead?

501
00:27:21,440 --> 00:27:21,880
Sure.

502
00:27:21,880 --> 00:27:23,080
If I use the my non-dominant hand, I'll fall to the floor.

503
00:27:23,080 --> 00:27:24,080
Okay.

504
00:27:25,000 --> 00:27:25,760
How many cards?

505
00:27:25,760 --> 00:27:26,760
Just one.

506
00:27:27,480 --> 00:27:28,480
Here you go.

507
00:27:33,760 --> 00:27:34,760
Ooh!

508
00:27:36,080 --> 00:27:37,080
Two of Diamonds.

509
00:27:38,840 --> 00:27:40,800
That means your work life is in decline.

510
00:27:40,800 --> 00:27:42,240
If you pull this card,

511
00:27:42,240 --> 00:27:44,280
you might be under scrutiny at work.

512
00:27:47,400 --> 00:27:48,400
Oh my!

513
00:27:49,320 --> 00:27:52,480
This card also means your career’s taking a dip.

514
00:27:52,480 --> 00:27:54,400
You could have problems with your boss.

515
00:27:54,400 --> 00:27:55,680
How do we fix it?

516
00:27:55,680 --> 00:27:59,680
You’ll need a photo of your boss.

517
00:28:02,080 --> 00:28:04,480
Why are these cards all so bad?

518
00:28:04,480 --> 00:28:07,560
Can I shuffle the deck myself once?

519
00:28:07,560 --> 00:28:09,560
Sure! Go ahead.

520
00:28:12,200 --> 00:28:13,720
Whoa, you’re better than a real reader.

521
00:28:16,920 --> 00:28:17,840
Sky!

522
00:28:17,840 --> 00:28:19,200
You shuffled all the faces off, just deal already!

523
00:28:19,200 --> 00:28:20,200
Oh, okay!

524
00:28:27,680 --> 00:28:30,440
Whoa! Lucky draw!

525
00:28:30,440 --> 00:28:32,720
A natural nine with a double!

526
00:28:32,720 --> 00:28:33,720
Ooh ooh! I got one too!

527
00:28:40,360 --> 00:28:41,360
Mine's really bad.

528
00:28:43,000 --> 00:28:45,000
Let me shuffle this time.

529
00:28:45,720 --> 00:28:46,720
This time, I’m the dealer.

530
00:28:48,560 --> 00:28:51,520
Wait, so we’re not doing fortunes anymore?

531
00:28:51,520 --> 00:28:53,560
Well...now we’re playing Pok Deng.

532
00:28:53,560 --> 00:28:54,640
Just passing time!

533
00:28:54,640 --> 00:28:55,960
Actually, that’s a good idea.

534
00:28:55,960 --> 00:28:57,000
Yeah, long-haul flights are so tiring.

535
00:28:57,000 --> 00:28:58,000
True!

536
00:28:58,880 --> 00:28:59,880
Just a little fun, right?

537
00:29:02,000 --> 00:29:06,000
Whoa, I really am lucky! Got Pok Deng again!

538
00:29:08,920 --> 00:29:09,920
Sky!

539
00:29:10,320 --> 00:29:11,160
Yes?

540
00:29:11,160 --> 00:29:12,160
Your wrist!

541
00:29:14,320 --> 00:29:15,320
Don’t be shy.

542
00:29:16,280 --> 00:29:17,280
Here you go.

543
00:29:18,040 --> 00:29:22,040
Hey, we’re just playing for fun. Don’t take it so seriously.

544
00:29:22,240 --> 00:29:23,240
Playing for fun?

545
00:29:23,520 --> 00:29:24,520
Don't take it so seriously?

546
00:29:25,680 --> 00:29:27,880
Don’t worry, when we go shopping...

547
00:29:28,200 --> 00:29:30,200
I'll take care of you girls.

548
00:29:32,200 --> 00:29:33,200
Thank you.

549
00:29:33,440 --> 00:29:35,400
But I do have one condition.

550
00:29:35,400 --> 00:29:39,320
I would like to exchange it for…

551
00:29:39,320 --> 00:29:42,680
information about Glamorous Airline.

552
00:29:42,680 --> 00:29:45,280
I want to pass it along to my niece.

553
00:29:45,280 --> 00:29:48,160
Oh…

554
00:29:48,160 --> 00:29:51,840
But to be honest, exclusive info like that,

555
00:29:51,840 --> 00:29:55,840
only Diamond-level staff know it.

556
00:29:55,960 --> 00:30:01,960
Oh come on! How would I know any Diamond-level crew?

557
00:30:03,880 --> 00:30:08,880
Oh! Don’t tell me, you, Sky and Chaba, are you two…

558
00:30:10,520 --> 00:30:12,640
Of course.

559
00:30:12,640 --> 00:30:16,640
Oh wow, I'm so happy to hear that!

560
00:30:17,840 --> 00:30:19,840
Let’s go another round, shall we?

561
00:30:20,360 --> 00:30:21,360
Let’s stop already.

562
00:30:27,960 --> 00:30:30,640
Only this game is fair.

563
00:30:30,640 --> 00:30:31,840
Bring it on!

564
00:30:31,840 --> 00:30:34,480
This game is about “Four.”

565
00:30:34,480 --> 00:30:35,800
Four Mod?

566
00:30:35,800 --> 00:30:36,800
No, 4EVE.

567
00:30:38,280 --> 00:30:40,800
Ready? Go!

568
00:30:42,480 --> 00:30:42,960
Mind.

569
00:30:42,960 --> 00:30:44,640
Atitaya.

570
00:30:44,640 --> 00:30:45,200
Jorin.

571
00:30:45,200 --> 00:30:46,920
Khumpiraphan.

572
00:30:46,920 --> 00:30:47,600
Taaom.

573
00:30:47,600 --> 00:30:48,560
Benyapa.

574
00:30:48,560 --> 00:30:49,200
Hannah.

575
00:30:49,200 --> 00:30:51,080
Rosenbloom.

576
00:30:51,080 --> 00:30:52,440
Fai-Nattaya.

577
00:30:52,440 --> 00:30:53,600
Punch-Tipanan.

578
00:30:53,600 --> 00:30:54,840
Aheye-Korranid.

579
00:30:54,840 --> 00:30:56,640
4.E.V.E.-4EVE.

580
00:30:56,640 --> 00:30:58,640
4EVE for aye. Yeah!

581
00:31:00,800 --> 00:31:02,160
That was excellent!

582
00:31:02,160 --> 00:31:04,800
Well, that's your generation!

583
00:31:04,800 --> 00:31:06,480
Of course, you could memorize it.

584
00:31:06,480 --> 00:31:07,520
Well, I can't help you with that.

585
00:31:07,520 --> 00:31:08,520
You were born first.

586
00:31:10,440 --> 00:31:12,440
You want a piece of me?

587
00:31:14,160 --> 00:31:15,120
Noom-Kanchai.

588
00:31:15,120 --> 00:31:16,280
Noom-Sornram.

589
00:31:16,280 --> 00:31:17,440
Bird-Thongchai.

590
00:31:17,440 --> 00:31:18,480
Mos-Patipan.

591
00:31:18,480 --> 00:31:19,600
Jeng-Big Ass.

592
00:31:19,600 --> 00:31:20,920
Toon-Bodyslam.

593
00:31:20,920 --> 00:31:22,120
Oat Pramote.

594
00:31:22,120 --> 00:31:22,760
Tik-Jes.

595
00:31:22,760 --> 00:31:23,600
Lift and Oil.

596
00:31:23,600 --> 00:31:24,440
Jason Young.

597
00:31:24,440 --> 00:31:25,160
Leo Put.

598
00:31:25,160 --> 00:31:26,240
Doo-Sanya.

599
00:31:26,240 --> 00:31:28,240
Dag-Big Ass! There you go!

600
00:31:31,040 --> 00:31:33,040
Now we know how old you are.

601
00:31:34,080 --> 00:31:35,200
But I gotta give you two thumbs up for that.

602
00:31:35,200 --> 00:31:36,200
Right.

603
00:31:36,320 --> 00:31:38,560
Well, you won because you're old.

604
00:31:38,560 --> 00:31:40,000
Damn you! Don't you know when  to stop?

605
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:41,520
You wanna get slapped?

606
00:31:41,520 --> 00:31:42,520
Hey!

607
00:31:42,720 --> 00:31:43,720
Save your energy to breathe first.

608
00:31:52,560 --> 00:31:55,000
This next game will be the final decider.

609
00:31:55,000 --> 00:31:57,960
Final game? Then shouldn’t there be a bet?

610
00:31:57,960 --> 00:31:59,320
What kind of bet?

611
00:31:59,320 --> 00:32:03,320
Whoever gets the right answer…gets to slap.

612
00:32:04,280 --> 00:32:06,120
Can you even handle that?

613
00:32:06,120 --> 00:32:09,880
Hey, Tid-Gift, trust me, you can’t beat her.

614
00:32:10,480 --> 00:32:12,480
You clearly don’t know me well enough.

615
00:32:15,480 --> 00:32:17,960
Alright then. This game is: name a princess.

616
00:32:17,960 --> 00:32:18,960
Snow White.

617
00:32:22,400 --> 00:32:23,400
Sano Noi Ruean Ngam.

618
00:32:25,160 --> 00:32:26,160
What the hell was that?

619
00:32:26,280 --> 00:32:27,280
She's a princess too. Deal with it.

620
00:32:28,520 --> 00:32:29,520
Alright.

621
00:32:30,720 --> 00:32:31,720
Ariel.

622
00:32:33,040 --> 00:32:34,040
Kaew Na Ma.

623
00:32:37,320 --> 00:32:38,320
Cinderella.

624
00:32:42,720 --> 00:32:43,720
Damn, that was quite a slap.

625
00:32:45,880 --> 00:32:47,880
Pla Bu Thong.

626
00:32:55,640 --> 00:32:57,640
Moana.

627
00:33:01,680 --> 00:33:02,680
Pikul Thong.

628
00:33:05,720 --> 00:33:06,720
Jasmine.

629
00:33:07,680 --> 00:33:08,680
That's enough.

630
00:33:10,600 --> 00:33:11,600
Kreetha.

631
00:33:17,120 --> 00:33:18,120
How are you doing?

632
00:33:23,600 --> 00:33:24,600
That's blood...

633
00:33:32,040 --> 00:33:33,040
Did you hit me?

634
00:33:33,240 --> 00:33:34,240
I don't know who did that.

635
00:33:35,040 --> 00:33:36,040
I didn't see anyone.

636
00:33:36,800 --> 00:33:37,800
Ouch.

637
00:33:40,640 --> 00:33:41,760
Ladies and gentlemen...

638
00:33:41,760 --> 00:33:45,760
We have now landed in Bangkok.

639
00:33:46,080 --> 00:33:48,920
We are delighted...

640
00:33:48,920 --> 00:33:51,000
to be your airline of choice.

641
00:33:51,000 --> 00:33:53,720
Please check your belongings before disembarking.

642
00:33:53,720 --> 00:33:56,960
Thank you for flying with Glamorous Airline.

643
00:33:56,960 --> 00:34:00,480
We look forward to seeing you again.

644
00:34:00,480 --> 00:34:01,440
Thank you.

645
00:34:01,440 --> 00:34:02,440
And goodbye.

646
00:34:02,840 --> 00:34:03,840
Thank you.

647
00:34:08,560 --> 00:34:09,560
Sky, dear…

648
00:34:15,160 --> 00:34:17,200
about what we agreed on earlier...

649
00:34:17,200 --> 00:34:18,200
what’s your decision?

650
00:34:19,360 --> 00:34:21,360
I’m actually selling company secrets to you, Pam.

651
00:34:33,880 --> 00:34:35,880
I'll transfer the money for you.

652
00:34:38,920 --> 00:34:39,840
Thank you.

653
00:34:39,840 --> 00:34:40,840
Goodbye.

654
00:34:45,240 --> 00:34:46,480
See that?

655
00:34:46,680 --> 00:34:50,680
All it took was flashing some cash and those two were instantly on our side.

656
00:34:50,960 --> 00:34:52,040
Exactly.

657
00:34:52,040 --> 00:34:55,840
Wait, Miji, why are you speaking Japanese when it’s just us?

658
00:34:55,840 --> 00:34:58,720
Why, Madam?

659
00:34:58,720 --> 00:35:00,960
Why is it always my fault?

660
00:35:00,960 --> 00:35:04,960
Why are you sensitive when you're Miji?

661
00:35:15,920 --> 00:35:16,920
Sky.

662
00:35:17,200 --> 00:35:20,800
We gave them next to nothing, and came back with a pile of handbags.

663
00:35:20,800 --> 00:35:22,080
Totally worth it.

664
00:35:22,080 --> 00:35:24,080
Seriously, they were ridiculously easy to trick.

665
00:35:38,320 --> 00:35:39,800
Thanks for coming to see me off.

666
00:35:43,200 --> 00:35:44,200
Does it hurt a lot?

667
00:35:44,560 --> 00:35:46,560
Oh please, Sai Eiam. Don’t even ask.

668
00:36:06,040 --> 00:36:07,040
Hello, Dad?

669
00:36:08,720 --> 00:36:12,280
I’m really sorry I couldn’t collect the debt this time.

670
00:36:12,280 --> 00:36:14,840
Next time, I’ll come back and get it, I promise.

671
00:36:14,840 --> 00:36:17,880
Sai Eiam, do you think I didn’t know...

672
00:36:17,880 --> 00:36:19,800
why you really went there?

673
00:36:19,800 --> 00:36:21,280
The person I had following you...

674
00:36:21,280 --> 00:36:23,000
reported everything.

675
00:36:23,000 --> 00:36:24,000
Look at the photos.

676
00:36:34,080 --> 00:36:39,080
Dad, come on! He still doesn't have it this time.

677
00:36:40,160 --> 00:36:42,600
Just let me come back and collect it later, okay?

678
00:36:42,600 --> 00:36:45,680
Please? Please, Dad? Pretty please?

679
00:36:45,680 --> 00:36:46,560
No.

680
00:36:46,560 --> 00:36:49,960
There it is! I knew it! Dad, you’re the best in the world.

681
00:36:49,960 --> 00:36:51,640
I’ll head back now. Bye-bye!

682
00:36:51,640 --> 00:36:53,640
Sai Eiam! Sai Eiam!

683
00:36:55,240 --> 00:36:56,880
Sai Eiam!

684
00:36:56,880 --> 00:36:58,880
I’ll find a way to pay you back soon, okay?

685
00:37:02,160 --> 00:37:03,160
It’s fine.

686
00:37:04,200 --> 00:37:07,040
You don’t have to pay me back with money.

687
00:37:07,040 --> 00:37:11,040
You can pay me back with…other things.

688
00:37:20,160 --> 00:37:21,680
Ugh, not you again, Auntie.

689
00:37:21,680 --> 00:37:23,680
Why do you manage to be everywhere?

690
00:37:24,680 --> 00:37:25,680
Kreetha.

691
00:37:26,240 --> 00:37:29,200
About last night, I’m sorry.

692
00:37:29,200 --> 00:37:32,040
I didn’t mean to hit you.

693
00:37:32,040 --> 00:37:33,680
I’m sorry, does it hurt?

694
00:37:33,680 --> 00:37:35,680
Owwwwww.

695
00:37:36,240 --> 00:37:38,240
Sai Eiam, I, man...

696
00:37:38,240 --> 00:37:42,240
Also, can you tell that auntie I’m sorry too?

697
00:37:43,480 --> 00:37:46,160
I'm here.

698
00:37:46,160 --> 00:37:48,160
Just stop calling me an auntie, that'll do.

699
00:37:51,960 --> 00:37:54,640
Kreetha, about the debt...don’t worry.

700
00:37:54,640 --> 00:37:56,400
I’ll talk to my dad for you.

701
00:37:56,400 --> 00:38:00,400
Let’s meet again next time, okay?

702
00:38:01,040 --> 00:38:02,040
Okay.

703
00:38:02,520 --> 00:38:03,520
I'm off now.

704
00:38:04,280 --> 00:38:06,240
Go on! You’ll miss your flight.

705
00:38:06,240 --> 00:38:08,240
Off you go!

706
00:38:08,960 --> 00:38:10,840
I'm really leaving now, Kreetha.

707
00:38:10,840 --> 00:38:13,400
Sai Eiam, thank you so much...

708
00:38:13,400 --> 00:38:15,120
for telling me that you're gonna talk to your dad.

709
00:38:16,120 --> 00:38:17,240
It’s nothing.

710
00:38:17,240 --> 00:38:19,240
Then, safe travels, okay?

711
00:38:24,280 --> 00:38:25,280
Alright. Bye-bye!

712
00:38:31,000 --> 00:38:32,240
Go already!

713
00:38:32,240 --> 00:38:34,240
You'll miss your flight.

714
00:38:34,800 --> 00:38:36,800
Go on! Hurry up!

715
00:38:44,280 --> 00:38:46,280
Let's get to the office. We got a meeting.

716
00:38:48,760 --> 00:38:51,520
Oh, you're still hurting?

717
00:38:51,520 --> 00:38:53,560
You were fine last night.

718
00:38:53,560 --> 00:38:56,280
Well, I thought so too.

719
00:38:56,280 --> 00:38:57,800
But when I wore them again, they gave me blisters.

720
00:38:57,800 --> 00:38:59,800
I guess I'll need a new pair of shoes.

721
00:39:09,920 --> 00:39:10,480
Let's go.

722
00:39:10,480 --> 00:39:12,480
Easy, easy there.

723
00:39:16,880 --> 00:39:17,880
How is it, All-New?

724
00:39:19,320 --> 00:39:22,080
I think this is getting too llight for me.

725
00:39:22,080 --> 00:39:23,840
I meant...the information.

726
00:39:23,840 --> 00:39:24,840
Oh, that.

727
00:39:26,280 --> 00:39:27,880
I've taken a look at that.

728
00:39:27,880 --> 00:39:30,400
The flash drive that you got is empty.

729
00:39:30,400 --> 00:39:31,400
Huh?

730
00:39:33,480 --> 00:39:35,600
There's always something good, even in the bad.

731
00:39:35,600 --> 00:39:37,560
Oh, really? What is that?

732
00:39:37,560 --> 00:39:39,560
Well, you got one flash drive for free.

733
00:39:41,080 --> 00:39:43,840
I paid thousands of Baht for that!

734
00:39:43,840 --> 00:39:47,560
Madam, if you're done talking to me, let me continue my workout.

735
00:39:47,560 --> 00:39:49,560
Looks like you're enjoying this.

736
00:39:50,760 --> 00:39:51,760
Not really.

737
00:40:05,360 --> 00:40:06,360
Siri!

738
00:40:06,560 --> 00:40:07,560
Siri!

739
00:40:09,640 --> 00:40:10,640
Where are you?

740
00:40:17,360 --> 00:40:19,240
Siri, where are you?

741
00:40:19,240 --> 00:40:22,280
Have you found me an automaton?

742
00:40:22,280 --> 00:40:24,280
Of course, it's in your office.

743
00:40:25,520 --> 00:40:26,520
Where?

744
00:40:27,200 --> 00:40:28,200
It's there, in your room.

745
00:40:29,320 --> 00:40:31,880
Hey, when did it get here?

746
00:40:31,880 --> 00:40:32,880
For a while.

747
00:40:34,560 --> 00:40:35,560
Oh?

748
00:40:36,800 --> 00:40:39,600
Ooh, this is enormous!

749
00:40:39,600 --> 00:40:41,000
How do I open this?

750
00:40:41,000 --> 00:40:42,880
You gotta knock on the box first.

751
00:40:42,880 --> 00:40:43,760
How many times?

752
00:40:43,760 --> 00:40:44,760
Three.

753
00:40:46,840 --> 00:40:48,840
Three cha-cha's.

754
00:41:04,000 --> 00:41:05,000
Hey!

755
00:41:07,080 --> 00:41:11,080
I'm here, ready to serve you.

756
00:41:11,680 --> 00:41:14,360
I told you to get me a Thai spirit automaton.

757
00:41:14,360 --> 00:41:16,160
Not a robot.

758
00:41:16,160 --> 00:41:17,720
Well, this is quite the same.

759
00:41:17,720 --> 00:41:18,960
I want an automaton!

760
00:41:18,960 --> 00:41:21,040
Well, this is it.

761
00:41:21,040 --> 00:41:24,040
Siri! What the hell are you talking about?

762
00:41:28,720 --> 00:41:31,400
Well, since you're here...

763
00:41:31,400 --> 00:41:32,720
what can you do?

764
00:41:32,720 --> 00:41:35,880
I can carry out your every order, Master.

765
00:41:35,880 --> 00:41:38,880
Then, move this plant pot.

766
00:41:38,880 --> 00:41:39,880
Yes, Master.

767
00:41:49,880 --> 00:41:50,880
Action executed successfully.

768
00:41:51,200 --> 00:41:53,200
Let's move it back.

769
00:41:59,800 --> 00:42:00,800
Action executed successfully.

770
00:42:01,120 --> 00:42:02,120
Let's put it here.

771
00:42:17,080 --> 00:42:18,520
Oh, Siri!

772
00:42:18,520 --> 00:42:19,800
Siri!

773
00:42:19,800 --> 00:42:20,800
Oh!

774
00:42:22,160 --> 00:42:24,160
Serves you right!

775
00:42:37,880 --> 00:42:39,720
So how's my total look today?

776
00:42:39,720 --> 00:42:41,440
Can I be the luxurious Miss Sky?

777
00:42:41,440 --> 00:42:43,160
Let me be totally honest with you.

778
00:42:43,160 --> 00:42:44,480
Your look is very expensive.

779
00:42:44,480 --> 00:42:48,480
More expensive than the current market price of gold...

780
00:42:48,600 --> 00:42:50,840
Well, I guess I have Pam's stupidity to thank for this.

781
00:42:50,840 --> 00:42:53,840
How could anyone possibly access information that confidential?

782
00:42:55,120 --> 00:42:57,440
Pam, you got money but you got no brain.

783
00:42:57,440 --> 00:42:58,440
We can't help you with that.

784
00:42:58,960 --> 00:42:59,960
Let's go. It's time to fly.

785
00:43:00,960 --> 00:43:01,960
True.

786
00:43:02,280 --> 00:43:05,080
Don't tell me you're gonna do that.

787
00:43:05,320 --> 00:43:06,840
I'm not gonna do it. It's too corny.

788
00:43:10,040 --> 00:43:11,040
Right, too corny.

789
00:43:11,800 --> 00:43:12,800
Don't tell me...

790
00:43:17,600 --> 00:43:18,600
You're so silly.

791
00:43:22,960 --> 00:43:24,080
Hmm...

792
00:43:25,440 --> 00:43:26,280
What's wrong?

793
00:43:26,280 --> 00:43:27,320
I...

794
00:43:27,320 --> 00:43:29,720
I'm scared of this woman's wrinkles!

795
00:43:29,720 --> 00:43:30,720
I'm panicking. I'm about to faint.

796
00:43:32,400 --> 00:43:33,400
Let's go, Kreetha.

797
00:43:33,680 --> 00:43:34,680
Smells like...old people.

798
00:43:36,800 --> 00:43:37,800
The air is so toxic.

799
00:43:45,680 --> 00:43:48,200
So what's Mr. Glam like?

800
00:43:48,760 --> 00:43:51,480
Oh, you mean my boss, Mr. Glam?

801
00:43:51,480 --> 00:43:53,680
Well, he's one of a kind.

802
00:43:53,680 --> 00:43:55,960
Great figure.

803
00:43:55,960 --> 00:43:57,720
Tall. Lean.

804
00:43:57,720 --> 00:43:59,200
Narrow eyes with glasses...

805
00:43:59,200 --> 00:44:00,640
Mazda lips.

806
00:44:00,640 --> 00:44:01,800
Mercedes face.

807
00:44:01,800 --> 00:44:03,160
I, I don't think...

808
00:44:03,160 --> 00:44:07,160
I don't think it's the right line.

809
00:44:08,200 --> 00:44:09,000
Mazda lips.

810
00:44:09,000 --> 00:44:09,920
Cockle eyes.

811
00:44:09,920 --> 00:44:10,520
Ah, alright, alright.

812
00:44:11,000 --> 00:44:13,480
This is enormous! How do I open it?

813
00:44:13,720 --> 00:44:15,200
You gotta knock on the box.

814
00:44:16,600 --> 00:44:18,600
3 times. Cha-cha.

815
00:44:19,360 --> 00:44:20,360
Oh?

816
00:44:33,720 --> 00:44:35,000
We enjoy watching you.

817
00:44:35,000 --> 00:44:36,000
Is that so?

818
00:44:36,640 --> 00:44:38,520
If you want to compete,

819
00:44:38,520 --> 00:44:40,520
why don’t we try something else?

820
00:44:41,360 --> 00:44:42,360
Come on.

821
00:44:54,920 --> 00:44:55,920
Why don’t we try something else?

822
00:44:56,280 --> 00:44:57,280
Come on!

823
00:45:12,400 --> 00:45:13,400
Ooh, that was tiring.

824
00:45:14,320 --> 00:45:15,320
That's really tiring.

825
00:45:17,160 --> 00:45:20,040
I never thought that I'd see you here.

826
00:45:21,080 --> 00:45:22,080
Her name is Keerati.

827
00:45:22,240 --> 00:45:24,960
We'd been competing to be the best in the past.

828
00:45:24,960 --> 00:45:27,960
I won't give in to you anymore.

829
00:45:30,040 --> 00:45:31,360
Mr. Glam, don't you worry.

830
00:45:32,360 --> 00:45:33,680
The kill team. Same crew.

831
00:45:34,120 --> 00:45:35,120
The kill team?

832
00:45:35,560 --> 00:45:37,920
Trust me, no one's walking out.

833
00:45:38,200 --> 00:45:39,560
Just death and more death.

834
00:45:39,560 --> 00:45:40,560
Death and more death?

835
00:45:40,880 --> 00:45:42,280
Am I about to get taken out by Glam?
